text: Anarsia spatulana is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It was described by Kyu-Tek Park and Margarita Gennadievna Ponomarenko in 1996. It is found in Thailand. The wingspan is 17–18 mm. The forewings are grey with a large dark brown costal mark. The hindwings are pale grey. ==References== spatulana Category:Moths described in 1996 Category:Moths of Asia
